metadata.name: The Weight of Winter #26
metadata.description:
Description of Seasons of Siskiyou Series

Surrounding my home, covering more than one million acres, is the Rogue River - Siskiyou National Forest which takes up three southern Oregon counties and one northern California county.  It’s a magical place that fills the imagination and lifts the spirit; a place that inspires with its uniqueness, its legends, and its larger-than-life vistas.

Each season in the Siskiyous is a unique experience unto itself.  So, with an attention to the feelings this place evokes at any given time of the year, I designed four generative tokens to create an impression of the emotion–the calming quietness; the peaceful solitude; the overwhelming contrasts and variety of forms, shapes and textures; the magic and playful mystery; the welcomingness and foreboding.  These four works feature clever and inventive creative coding techniques in a rich, graphic style to craft a stunning impression of the Seasons of Siskiyou.


Token 4 of 4 - The Weight of Winter (1990 x 1080) p5js Generative Token.

All good things must come to an end.  After a glorious time of renewal and rebirth, the months of growth and bounty come to a close.  A time of reflection and rest approaches.  All that can be done has been done; and, all one can do is endure the season of slumber.

As light fades with the shyness of the sun, the need to sleep takes over as the creatures of the wilderness test their preparedness.  Travelers to warner lands have offered farewell to those brave enough to stand against the coming snows.  Those who have remained will carry the weight of winter.  The festival of fall had provided so much to carry them through to the colors of spring.  Has it been enough?

The weight of winter can be crushing; but, it’s the pressure that shapes the designs of persistence, endurance and perseverance required to fight against it.  With its paler of indifference, the monochrome landscape of winter hides the brilliance of those schemes aimed at mastering the challenges of survival.  With their perfect adaptations, nature survives to take on winter’s heft with defiant joyfulness and triumphant serenity.  

The Weight of Winter features a generative atmosphere with distant mountains; flow-field conifer trees on noise-wave foothills; a random cluster of subject conifers in the mid-space; and a flow-field tree branch with an interpolated dusting of snow.  Diamond dust – small spears of ice – are simulated with an optical-effect along with random snowflakes.  A generative ‘conspiracy’ of ravens are scattered along the tree tops.

Once the scene is completely generated, a framing box will appear.  Press the DOWN ARROW to save the scene as a png image file.  Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.

Token Published May 9, 2022 on FXHASH set at 75 Editions.
Written and designed by Ed Cavett using the p5js library.
Token 4 of 4 from the series “The Seasons of Siskiyou.”

metadata.name: Outside your Window #51
metadata.description:
Never take for granted that we sit in the safety of our homes, behind our windows, sheltered from the elements outside. 

The characteristics of the rain outside the window, and the window itself, will be determined by the mint hash. However, the background color of this piece will constantly change based on the hour of day it is loaded, hence note that the thumbnail will only technically be accurate 1/24 hours out of the day as it represents a static snapshot taken at the time of token rendering.

100% of the primary proceeds will be donated towards flood relief efforts for the devastating December 2021 floods in Malaysia.

Made in p5js
Created December 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Ersbla #679
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #430
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js
